whisper_transcription: Which form of testosterone is the best for TRT? Tessiponate or Sustanon? When doing TRT, it is more ideal to use Tessiponate and here's why. It's going to be more stable in your system with only having to do an injection frequency of about once a week. And since it is only one ester and it's a longer ester, that means your hormone levels are going to stay a lot more stable throughout the process. Using something like Sustanon is not ideal because you're going to be having a form of testosterone that's a combination of different esters, which means your hormones are more likely to be fluctuating and you'd also have to do more frequent injections, which is not ideal. When it comes to TRT, I highly recommend you choose Testosterone Siponate because it's the best choice to optimize your testosterone levels.

whisper_transcription: If I had one month left to live and I had to cut down into the best shape of my life, this would be my degenerate diet. Straight up, 1400 calories, 200 grams of protein. Meal number one, 95 grams of salmon and one serving of EAAs, around 155 calories. Meal number two is 250 grams of kangaroo and one egg, this is around like 330 calories. Pre-workout was two LCM bars and another serving of EAAs, 195 calories. Post-workout, protein shake, 185. And finally we get to dinner. Dinner was 250 grams of kangaroo mince, two eggs and one thing of mixed leaf lettuce, that was 415 calories. This diet made me lose eight kilos in four weeks which is ridiculous, getting me down to the leanest I've ever been. But I also added around 10,000 to 20,000 steps every single day of those four weeks. So losing a lot of fat in a short period of time is possible.
